ce%20then%2C%20the%20nuclear%20family%20has%20crumbled%20piece%20by%20piece.%20In%201970%2C%20more%20than%20two-thirds%20of%20American%20adults%20between%2025%20and%2049%20lived%20with%20a%20spouse%20and%20at%20least%20one%20kid.%20By%202021%2C%20only%2037%25%20of%20adults%20fit%20the%20bill%2C%20Pew%20Research%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20it%20may%20be%20premature%20to%20declare%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-marriage-family-structure-kids-over-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20nuclear%20family%20officially%20over%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20model%20is%20beginning%20to%20look%20more%20like%20a%20fringe%20lifestyle%20choice%20than%20the%20bedrock%20of%20American%20society.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20demise%20has%20sparked%20no%20shortage%20of%20(often%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dissentmagazine.org%2Farticle%2Fmoynihan-report-resurrected-daniel-geary-black-power%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eracist%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2F5405100%2Fmurphy-brown-cultural-importance-reboot%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esexist%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.govtrack.us%2Fcongress%2Fbills%2F104%2Fhr3396%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehomophobic%3C%2Fa%3E)%20political%20backlash.%20From%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpronatalism-elon-musk-simone-malcolm-collins-underpopulation-breeding-tech-2022-11%3Fr%3Dmusk-peel%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EElon%20Musk%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20father%20of%2011%20kids%2C%20to%20the%20failed%20GOP%20presidential%20hopeful%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3D-eRHH8qOl44%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVivek%20Ramaswamy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20defenders%20of%20so-called%20%26quot%3Btraditional%20family%20values%26quot%3B%20decry%20the%20potential%20economic%20hazards%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgreat-labor-shortage-looming-population-decline-disaster-global-economy-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eplummeting%20birth%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20social%20disorder%20caused%20by%20unruly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aei.org%2Fop-eds%2Fwhat-liberals-dont-understand-about-men-and-marriage%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emen%20without%20wives%20to%20rein%20them%20in%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Some%20even%20argue%20that%20the%20nuclear%20family%20is%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cairn.info%2Frevue-francaise-d-etudes-americaines-2003-3-page-7.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecornerstone%20of%20democracy%3C%2Fa%3E%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224113%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Two%20young%20boys%20in%20shorts%20run%20to%20greet%20Dad%20coming%20home%20from%20work%20while%20Mother%20is%20standing%20in%20the%20background.%20Circa%201960%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66045b7d1caec1275a6a0269%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225100%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFor%20decades%2C%20the%20idea%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Bfamily%26quot%3B%20consisted%20of%20a%20married%20couple%20with%20two%20kids.%3Cp%3ECamerique%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOthers%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20have%20eagerly%20cheered%20on%20the%20shift%20away%20from%20the%20stifling%20gender%20politics%20of%20the%20four-person%20norm.%20Critics%20include%20radical%20family-abolition%20scholars%20such%20as%20M.E.%20O'Brien%2C%20whose%202023%20book%20%26quot%3BFamily%20Abolition%3A%20Capitalism%20and%20the%20Communizing%20of%20Care%26quot%3B%20argues%20that%20the%20contained%20family%20structures%20%26quot%3Bcannot%20carry%20the%20immense%20burden%20of%20work%20placed%20on%20them.%26quot%3B%20On%20the%20other%20end%20of%20the%20political%20spectrum%2C%20in%20an%20early%202020%20cover%20story%20for%20The%20Atlantic%3Cem%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethe%20conservative%20columnist%20David%20Brooks%20declared%20the%20nuclear%20family%20%26quot%3Ba%20mistake.%26quot%3B%20Since%20the%20onset%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20the%20looming%20cloud%20of%20skepticism%20hanging%20over%20the%20whole%20concept%20of%20the%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-changed-typical-american-family-structure-2019-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enuclear%20family%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20has%20only%20thickened.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20it%20or%20hate%20it%2C%20the%20future%20of%20the%20family%20has%20never%20appeared%20so%20uncertain.%20For%20a%20society%20structured%20around%20the%20ideal%20of%20the%20nuclear%20family%2C%20its%20demise%20has%20left%20everyone%20wondering%3A%20What%20happens%20now%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20many%20other%20social%20norms%2C%20the%20nuclear%20family%20was%20the%20product%20of%20the%20economic%20and%20cultural%20conditions%20of%20a%20particular%20time%20and%20place%2C%20upheld%20by%20policies%20and%20institutions%20for%20decades.%20Until%20the%2019th%20century%2C%20marriage%20was%20less%20the%20union%20of%20two%20souls%20in%20love%20than%20the%20pragmatic%2C%20obligatory%20step%20in%20a%20long%20tradition%20of%20social%20and%20family%20organization.%20Most%20Americans%20at%20that%20time%20lived%20in%20extended%2C%20multigenerational%20%26quot%3Bcorporate%20families%26quot%3B%20that%20worked%20together%20to%20run%20a%20family%20farm%20or%20a%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20economy%20industrialized%20over%20the%20course%20of%20the%2019th%20century%2C%20more%20young%20men%20and%20women%20left%20their%20family%20farms%20for%20jobs%20in%20factories%20and%20offices%2C%20usually%20in%20cities.%20Free%20from%20the%20watchful%20eyes%20of%20their%20parents%20and%20relatives%2C%20these%20young%20people%20began%20to%20go%20on%20dates%2C%20spending%20their%20discretionary%20income%20on%20outings%20to%20the%20local%20movie%20house%20or%20soda%20counter.%20In%20her%202016%20book%20%26quot%3BLabor%20of%20Love%3A%20The%20Invention%20of%20Dating%3Cem%3E%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%26quot%3B%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3EMoira%20Weigel%20traced%20this%20shift.%20%26quot%3BBy%20bringing%20courtship%20out%20of%20the%20home%20and%20into%20the%20marketplace%2C%20dating%20became%20a%20lucrative%20business%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BFor%20the%20first%20time%20in%20human%20history%2C%20dating%20made%20it%20necessary%20to%20buy%20things%20in%20order%20to%20get%20face%20time%20with%20a%20prospective%20partner.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoving-dating-midwest-pandemic-transplants-california-coastal-attitude-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edating%20culture%3C%2Fa%3E%20became%20more%20entrenched%20in%20the%20economy%20during%20the%2020th%20century%2C%20a%20community-based%20way%20of%20life%20gave%20way%20to%20individuals%20focusing%20on%20their%20own%20wants%20and%20needs.%20The%20middle%20class%20expanded%20and%20children%20were%20no%20longer%20expected%20to%20work%20for%20their%20family's%20economic%20survival%3B%20in%20white%2C%20middle-class%20families%2C%20men%20earned%20the%20wages%20that%20supported%20the%20family%20and%20their%20wives%20raised%20the%20children%20and%20ran%20the%20home.%20The%20nuclear%20family%20became%20a%20microcosm%20of%20capitalist%20self-sufficiency%20and%20the%20consumerism%20that%20came%20with%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20also%2C%20in%20some%20respects%2C%20a%20fluke.%20As%20Brooks%20noted%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theatlantic.com%2Fmagazine%2Farchive%2F2020%2F03%2Fthe-nuclear-family-was-a-mistake%2F605536%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Atlantic%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethe%20nuclear%20family's%20status%20as%20the%20default%20household%20arrangement%20for%20American%20adults%20peaked%20during%20the%20relatively%20brief%20window%20between%201950%20and%201965%2C%20when%20divorce%20rates%20plunged%2C%20fertility%20rates%20boomed%2C%20and%20the%20postwar%20economy%20flourished.%20It%20was%20during%20these%20years%20that%20%26quot%3Ba%20kind%20of%20cult%20formed%20around%20this%20type%20of%20family%2C%26quot%3B%20Brooks%20wrote%2C%20noting%20that%20those%20who%20broke%20the%20mold%20by%20opting%20out%20of%20marriage%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2012%2F02%2F21%2Fopinion%2Fbrooks-the-talent-society.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoften%20seen%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20deviant%20or%20%26quot%3Bneurotic.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223980%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Tract%20homes%20in%20suburban%20development%2C%20homes%2C%20lawns%2C%20driveways%20and%20roads%20comprise%20a%20typical%20suburban%20neighborhood%2C%20circa%201967%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66045b1616bde8d4ead2b770%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223182%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20nuclear%20family%20was%20a%20brief%20product%20of%20the%20postwar%20economic%20boom.%3Cp%3ECharles%20E.%20Rotkin%2FCorbis%2FVCG%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20obsession%20with%20the%20nuclear%20family%20masked%20its%20underlying%20instability.%20By%20the%201970s%2C%20social%20inequality%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fshort-reads%2F2018%2F08%2F07%2Ffor-most-us-workers-real-wages-have-barely-budged-for-decades%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewage%20stagnation%3C%2Fa%3E%20following%20the%201973%20oil%20crisis%20and%20recession%20had%20made%20it%20impossible%20for%20many%20white%2C%20middle-income%20husbands%20to%20sustain%20entire%20broods%20on%20a%20single%20salary.%20More%20and%20more%20women%20entered%20the%20workforce%2C%20giving%20them%20greater%20economic%20autonomy%20and%20enabling%20some%20to%20leave%20unhappy%20marriages.%20After%20California%20legalized%20no-fault%20divorce%20in%201969%2C%20other%20states%20quickly%20followed.%20In%20turn%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-celebrities-are-getting-divorced-society-is-changing-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edivorce%20rates%20soared%3C%2Fa%3E.%20(To%20this%20day%2C%20women%20initiate%20the%20overwhelming%20majority%20of%20divorces.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20nuclear%20family%20began%20to%20rapidly%20disintegrate.%20But%20it%20wasn't%20exactly%20the%20end%20of%20a%20golden%20era.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20more%20people%20have%20formed%20families%20that%20diverged%20from%20the%20nuclear-family%20norm%2C%20the%20weaknesses%20of%20the%20structure%20have%20become%20glaring.%20The%20biggest%20fallout%20we%20see%20today%20is%20in%20the%20childcare%20crisis%2C%20where%20the%20self-reliance%20inherent%20to%20the%20nuclear-family%20model%20resulted%20in%20women%20bearing%20the%20burden%20of%20raising%20children.%20Although%20an%20overwhelming%20majority%20of%20women%20now%20work%20outside%20the%20home%2C%20they%20continue%20to%20shoulder%20the%20bulk%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcare-economy-unpaid-work-minimum-wage-jobs-labor-infrastructure-bofa-2021-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunpaid%20caregiving%3C%2Fa%3E%20labor%20for%20children%20and%20aging%20relatives.%20They%20also%20end%20up%20doing%20more%20household%20chores%20%E2%80%94%20laundry%2C%20cleaning%2C%20and%20cooking%20are%20all%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.gallup.com%2Fpoll%2F286739%2Fworking-moms-little-reprieve-household-demands.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprimarily%20done%20by%20women%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithout%20one%20partner%20focused%20on%20full-time%20housekeeping%2C%20the%20amount%20of%20%3Cem%3Ework%3C%2Fem%3E%20required%20to%20run%20a%20nuclear%20family%20isn't%20really%20feasible.%20%26quot%3BAll%20families%2C%20without%20exception%2C%20are%20dependent%20on%20extensive%20outside%20support%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20that's%20state%20welfare%20programs%2C%20paid%20service%20people%2C%20or%20extended%20family%20members%20generously%20helping%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20O'Brien%2C%20the%20family-abolition%20author%2C%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20segmentation%20of%20families%20can%20also%20%26quot%3Bisolate%20vulnerable%20individuals%2C%20enabling%20abuse%2C%26quot%3B%20Stephanie%20Coontz%2C%20the%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BMarriage%2C%20a%20History%2C%26quot%3B%20told%20me.%20And%20%26quot%3Bsome%20such%20families%20consciously%20foster%20suspicion%20of%20those%20outside%20the%20family%20circle.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20this%20arrangement%20works%20nicely%20for%20the%20wealthiest%20%26quot%3Bshareholders%26quot%3B%20in%20a%20capitalist%20economic%20system%2C%20it%20isn't%20a%20particularly%20enticing%20deal%20for%20most%20Americans%2C%20Kristen%20Ghodsee%2C%20an%20ethnographer%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Pennsylvania%20and%20the%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BEveryday%20Utopia%3A%20In%20Praise%20of%20Radical%20Alternatives%20to%20the%20Traditional%20Family%20Home%2C%26quot%3B%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20declining%20birth%20rate%20in%20industrialized%20countries%20reflects%20the%20economic%20reality%20that%20children%20are%20a%20bad%20investment%20for%20families%2C%20and%20so%20many%20people%20are%20deciding%20not%20to%20have%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20Adjusting%20for%20future%20inflation%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.brookings.edu%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F08%2FBrookings_Cost-to-raise-a-child_inflation-adjusted-2.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBrookings%20Institution%3C%2Fa%3E%20estimated%20that%20it%20would%20cost%20%24310%2C605%20to%20raise%20a%20child%20born%20in%202015%20through%20age%2017%20%E2%80%94%20about%20%2443%2C000%20more%20in%20today's%20dollars%20than%20what%20it%20cost%20in%201960%20after%20adjusting%20for%20inflation.%20In%20a%202021%20Pew%20survey%20of%20child-free%20adults%20under%2050%2C%2044%25%20said%20they%20are%20unlikely%20to%20ever%20have%20children.%20When%20asked%20why%2C%20most%20responded%20that%20they%20simply%20don't%20want%20to.%20Nearly%20one%20in%20five%20said%20it%20was%20due%20to%20the%20cost.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGhodsee%20pointed%20out%20that%20while%20a%20smaller%20global%20population%20has%20its%20perks%20(the%20planet%20certainly%20isn't%20complaining)%2C%20it%20poses%20a%20serious%20threat%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-parents-dinks-childfree-boomers-economy-outlook-population-growth-birthrate-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elong-term%20economic%20growth%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BShrinking%20GDPs%20in%20the%20future%20are%20a%20direct%20result%20of%20shrinking%20populations%2C%20and%20that%20will%20challenge%20the%20very%20foundations%20of%20American%20capitalism%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20one%20reason%20why%20conservatives%20are%20so%20keen%20to%20limit%20women's%20reproductive%20freedoms.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20doesn't%20take%20much%20of%20a%20mental%20leap%20to%20see%20why%20capitalism%20and%20the%20nuclear%20family%20make%20for%20such%20cozy%20bedfellows.%20Atomized%20family%20units%20produce%20more%20market%20labor%20and%20buy%20greater%20quantities%20of%20%3Cem%3Estuff%3C%2Fem%3E%20than%20sprawling%2C%20communal%20kin%20groups%20that%20can%20lean%20on%20each%20other%20to%20share%20resources%20and%20manpower.%20The%20nuclear%20family's%20guise%20of%20self-sufficiency%20only%20barely%20conceals%20its%20toxic%20codependence%20with%20the%20market%20economy.%20But%20that%20dynamic%20also%20makes%20the%20nuclear%20family%20particularly%20vulnerable%20to%20economic%20pressures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20years%2C%20people%20who%20departed%20from%20the%20nuclear%20norm%20stopped%20being%20seen%20as%20aberrations%20and%20became%20examples%20of%20the%20varied%20paths%20adulthood%20could%20take.%20Today%2C%20nearly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fshort-reads%2F2019%2F12%2F12%2Fu-s-children-more-likely-than-children-in-other-countries-to-live-with-just-one-parent%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20quarter%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20children%20in%20the%20US%20live%20in%20single-parent%20households%2C%20and%20a%20rising%20share%20of%20adults%20live%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fsocial-trends%2F2021%2F10%2F05%2Frising-share-of-u-s-adults-are-living-without-a-spouse-or-partner%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewithout%20a%20spouse%20or%20romantic%20partner%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20either%20alone%20or%20with%20roommates.%20Where%20LGBTQ%2B%20partnership%20was%20once%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournalofethics.ama-assn.org%2Farticle%2Fdecriminalization-sodomy-united-states%2F2014-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecriminalized%3C%2Fa%3E%20across%20the%20country%2C%20same-sex%20unions%20are%20now%20sanctioned%20under%20federal%20law.%20As%20of%202020%2C%20even%20polyamorous%20families%20have%20gained%20legal%20protections%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2F19thnews.org%2F2023%2F04%2Fsomerville-massachusetts-legal-protections-polyamorous-families%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emunicipality%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20Somerville%2C%20Massachusetts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20growing%20diversity%20of%20household%20types%2C%20the%20nuclear%20family%20of%20the%201950s%20continues%20to%20shape%20the%20economics%20and%20institutions%20of%20American%20life.%20By%20and%20large%2C%20policies%20that%20inform%20tax%20systems%2C%20housing%2C%20healthcare%2C%20and%20social%20services%20are%20designed%20to%20provide%20the%20greatest%20benefit%20to%20married%20couples%20and%20their%20children.%20When%20my%20partner%20and%20I%20file%20our%20annual%20income%20taxes%20in%20the%20coming%20weeks%2C%20we'll%20enjoy%20a%20sizable%20tax%20break%20thanks%20to%20our%20decision%20to%20tie%20the%20knot%20last%20fall.%20And%20as%20a%20dependent%20on%20his%20employer-provided%20health-insurance%20plan%2C%20I'm%20able%20to%20make%20a%20living%20as%20a%20freelancer%20without%20worrying%20about%20healthcare%20coverage.%20But%20that%20narrow%20policy%20focus%20leaves%20an%20increasing%20numbers%20of%20Americans%20behind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20it's%20unclear%20what%20the%20family%20of%20the%20future%20will%20look%20like%2C%20seeds%20of%20change%20are%20blowing%20in%20the%20breeze.%20Recent%20months%20have%20seen%20a%20deluge%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnymag.com%2Fpress%2F2024%2F01%2Fon-the-cover-of-new-york-a-practical-guide-to-polyamory.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emagazine%20trend%20pieces%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reddit.com%2Fr%2Fpolyfamilies%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EReddit%20threads%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20newspaper%20headline%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F05%2F12%2Frealestate%2Fsingle-mother-households-co-living.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eportmanteaus%3C%2Fa%3E%20speculating%20about%20polyamorous%20families%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fplatonic-parenting-non-romantic-partners-choose-raise-kids-together-2021-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eplatonic%20coparenting%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsingle-moms-mommune-mothers-coliving-together-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emommunes%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20becoming%20the%20next%20big%20thing.%20Even%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-living-with-parents-save-money-housing-crisis-cost-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emultigenerational%20household%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20quietly%20coming%20back%20into%20vogue%2C%20thanks%20in%20large%20part%20to%20ongoing%20cost-of-living%20increases%20and%20families'%20caregiving%20needs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pandemic%20seemed%20to%20accelerate%20a%20collective%20sense%20of%20urgency%20to%20come%20up%20with%20something%20better.%20%26quot%3BIn%20order%20for%20